sentence: Tuesday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index at 6,333.01.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 1.65 billion.
Declining stocks led advancers by 2.02 to 1 ratio.
There were 980 advancers and 1975 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 29 stocks reached a 52 week high and 56 those reaching lows totaled.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed down -.01% for the day; a total of -.44 points.
Liberty Interactive Corporation ( QVCA ) had the largest percent change down (-4.42%) while Wynn Resorts, Limited ( WYNN ) had the largest percent change gain rising 6.41%.
The Dow Jones index closed up .02% for the day; a total of 5.28 points.
Home Depot, Inc. (The) ( HD ) had the largest percent change down (-2.65%) while American Express Company ( AXP ) had the largest percent change gain rising 1.54%.
